title: Best of Baltimore-area high school sports photos, week 4
text:
Oct 2, 2015 Best of Baltimore-area high school sports photos, week 4 45 Photos 
The best photos from Baltimore Sun Media Group photographers in week 4 of the fall 2015 high school sports season. Marriotts Ridge’s Jayme Choe, beats Centennial’s Reese Western to the ball during the girls soccer game at Centennial High School in Ellicott City, MD on Thursday, October 1, 2015. (Jen Rynda/BSMG) McDonogh’s Sarah Dohler, left, and Hannah Rothe, right, celebrate after beating Roland Park in a high school volleyball match in Owings MIlls, Thursday, Oct. 1, 2015. McDonogh won the match 3-1. (Photo by Steve Ruark) Hymad N’Diaye, center, of Oakland Mills reacts after missing a shot during a soccer game at Reservoir High School in Fulton on Friday, September 25, 2015. (Matt Hazlett/For BSMG) Westminster’s Jessie Karcz bumps the ball in front of teammate Sarah O’Donnell against Manchester Valley Thursday, Oct. 1 in Westminster. (Dave Munch/Caroll County Times) Spalding’s Joshua Chase pushes forward as Loyola moves in during Thursday nights game at Archbishop Spalding High School in Severn. (Matthew Cole/Capital Gazette) Francis Scott Key’s Skylar Lakin and Manchester Valley’s Jake Meredith fight for the ball Tuesday, Sept. 29 in Manchester. (Dave Munch/Carroll County Times) Freddie Duffey, left, of Catonsville and Muhammad Bobojonov of Franklin go for a header during a soccer game at Catonsville High School in Catonsville on Saturday, September 26, 2015. (Matt Hazlett/For BSMG) Lansdowne quarterback Antoine Jones, right, tries to outrun a tackle attempt by Towson’s Darren Cockerille during a football game at Towson High School on Friday, Sept. 25. (Brian Krista/BSMG) Marriotts Ridge’s Samantha Price, left, and Centennial’s Jasmine McCree, right, go up for the ball during the girls soccer game at Centennial High School in Ellicott City, MD on Thursday, October 1, 2015. (Jen Rynda/BSMG) Old Mill’s Jordyn Beans hits the ball in game two. The Old Mill Patriots defeated the visiting Glen Burnie Gophers in girls high school volleyball Tuesday night. (Paul W. Gillespie/Capital Gazette) Dulaney’s Emma Klein sends a shot in the direction of the Towson goal during a field hockey game at Dulaney High School on Tuesday, Sept. 29. (Brian Krista/BSMG) Howard’s Jackie Cherry hits the ball from the green on 18 during the 2015 Howard County Championship Golf Tournament at Hobbit’s Glen Golf Course in Columbia, MD on Tuesday, September 29, 2015. (Jen Rynda/BSMG) Wilde Lake’s Lee Lee Sands watches her tee shot off 17 through rain during the 2015 Howard County Championship Golf Tournament at Hobbit’s Glen Golf Course in Columbia, MD on Tuesday, September 29, 2015. (Jen Rynda/BSMG) Atholton’s Nick Osterman hits the ball out of the bunker on 9 during the 2015 Howard County Championship Golf Tournament at Hobbit’s Glen Golf Course in Columbia, MD on Tuesday, September 29, 2015. (Jen Rynda/BSMG) Gilman running back Dorian Maddox, right, breaks away from Loyola defensive lineman Trey Thomas, left, in the second quarter of a high school football game in Towson Friday, Sept. 25, 2015. (Photo by Steve Ruark) Severna Park’s Joshua Tucker leads the pack while competing in the boys varsity elite race at the Bull Run Invitational at Hereford High School Saturday, Sept. 26. (Dave Munch/Carroll County Times) Michael Ahumada, left, of Oakland Mills and Dutch Schulden of Reservoir go for a header during a soccer game at Reservoir High School in Fulton on Friday, September 25, 2015. (Matt Hazlett/For BSMG) Mt. Hebron’s Amanda Ross connects wth the ball during the second game of the volleyball match against Oakland Mills at Mt. Hebron High School in Ellicott City, MD on Tuesday, September 29, 2015. (Jen Rynda/BSMG) Towson goalie Kelsey Fringer makes a kick save on a shot by Dulaney’s Kiley Bolonda, right, during a field hockey game at Dulaney High School on Tuesday, Sept. 29. (Brian Krista/BSMG) Century takes on North Caroll Friday, Sept. 25 at Century High School. (Dave Munch/Carroll County Times) Francis Scott Key’s Trent Copenhaver fights for the ball in air with Manchester Valley’s Jake Meredith Tuesday, Sept. 29 in Manchester. (Dave Munch/Carroll County Times) Dulaney’s Calli Iouannou sends the ball in on a corner agaisnt Towson during a field hockey game at Dulaney High School on Tuesday, Sept. 29. (Brian Krista/BSMG) Arundel’s Larry Barnes scores on a 25-yard run in the second quarter. The visiting Arundel Wildcats played the Old Mill Patriots in boys high school football Friday evening. (Paul W. Gillespie/Capital Gazette) Arundel’s Andrew Cassard catches a pass in the second quarter. The visiting Arundel Wildcats played the Old Mill Patriots in boys high school football Friday evening. (Paul W. Gillespie/Capital Gazette) Towson’s Jackson Hays, left, can only get a few fingers on Lansdowne quarterback Antoine Jones who eludes a sack attempt during a football game at Towson High School on Friday, Sept. 25. (Brian Krista/BSMG) South Carroll’s Brian Cave nears the finish line in the boys varsity elite race while competeing at the Bull Run Invitational at Hereford High School Saturday, Sept. 26. (Dave Munch/Carroll County Times) Catonsville quarterback Danny Terzi, left, celebrates a touchdown pass with receiver Malik Baker against Franklin during a football game at Catonsville High School on Friday, Sept. 25. (Brian Krista/BSMG) Francis Scott Key’s Luke Luckenbaugh heads the ball past Manchester Valley’s Dayne Koontz Tuesday, Sept. 29 in Manchester. (Dave Munch/Carroll County Times) Century takes on North Caroll Friday, Sept. 25 at Century High School. (Dave Munch/Carroll County Times) Mckenzie Ali of Catonsville scores a goal during a soccer game at Catonsville High School in Catonsville on Saturday, September 26, 2015. (Matt Hazlett/For BSMG) St. Mary’s Caroline Feeley, right, gets the ball away from Severn’s Sydney Kirchenheiter in the second half. The St. Mary’s Saints defeated the visiting Severn Admirals, 3-1, in girl’s high school field hockey Wednesday afternoon. (Paul W. Gillespie/Capital Gazette) Century takes on North Caroll Friday, Sept. 25 at Century High School. (Dave Munch/Carroll County Times) Josh Dulaney of Catonsville runs down the ball during a soccer game at Catonsville High School in Catonsville on Saturday, September 26, 2015. (Matt Hazlett/For BSMG) Century takes on North Caroll Friday, Sept. 25 at Century High School. (Dave Munch/Carroll County Times) Luke Palmisano, left, of Catonsville tries to control the ball while Barazani Chiwengo of Franklin defends during a soccer game at Catonsville High School in Catonsville on Saturday, September 26, 2015. (Matt Hazlett/For BSMG) Gilman wide receiver Korey Stevens, third from left, tries to get away from Loyola defensive back Patrick Krack, left, and defensive end Dom Clark, right, as Gilman tight end Shane Lee, second from left, looks to block in the second quarter of a high school football game in Towson Friday, Sept. 25, 2015. (Photo by Steve Ruark) Marriotts Ridge’s Gabby Peitsch, right, tries to put the ball past Centennial’s Camryn Allen, left, and Rachel Mathew during the third game of the volleyball match at Centennial High School in Ellicott City, MD on Thursday, October 1, 2015. (Jen Rynda/BSMG) Luis Wardcantori, left, of Reservoir and teammate Justin Barnes walk off the field after being defeated by Oakland Mills during a soccer game at Reservoir High School in Fulton on Friday, September 25, 2015. (Matt Hazlett/For BSMG) Laurel’s Lyric Osazuwa digs a serve during a volleyball match against Bowie at Laurel High School on Thursday, Oct 1. (Brian Krista/BSMG) Severna Park’s Joshua Tucker and Dulaneys Eric Walz lead the pack while competing in the boys varsity elite race at the Bull Run Invitational at Hereford High School Saturday, Sept. 26. (Dave Munch/Carroll County Times) Spalding’s Evan Fochtman drives to the end zone as Loyola’s Rick Nickel works to keep up during Thursday nights game at Archbishop Spalding High School in Severn. (Matthew Cole/Capital Gazette) Centennial’s Ashley Molz boots the ball during the girls soccer game against Marriotts Ridge at Centennial High School in Ellicott City, MD on Thursday, October 1, 2015. (Jen Rynda/BSMG) South Carroll’s Malia Henry and Winters Mill’s Brynn Choplin meet at the net. (Ken Koons/Carroll County Times) Century takes on North Caroll Friday, Sept. 25 at Century High School. (Dave Munch/Carroll County Times)
